{"name": "dguad-vad", "metadata": {"name": "dguad-vad", "version": "0.1.0", "classifiers": ["Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Topic :: Scientific/Engineering"], "home_page": null, "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["librosa", "numpy", "onnxruntime", "soxr", "praat-parselmouth", "pyrnnoise"], "summary": null, "upload_time": 1733810156}, "documentation": ["# Dguard VAD\n\nBased on [Silero VAD](https://github.com/snakers4/silero-vad) and [RnNoise](https://github.com/werman/noise-suppression-for-voice).\n\n## Installation\n\n```bash\npip install dguard_vad\n```\nor\n```bash\ngit clone http://ai.lyxxkj.com.cn:3001/zhaosheng/dguard_vad.git\ncd dguard_vad\npip install -e .\n```\nThe model files will not be downloaded automatically.\nYou need to download them manually and put them in the right place.(Default: `$$DGUARD_MODEL_PATH/dguard_vad.onnx`)\n> $DGUARD_MODEL_PATH is an environment variable that used in all dgurad* projects.\n\n\n\n## Usage\n\n1. `VAD` class\n```python\nfrom dguard_vad import VAD\nSR = 16000\nWAV_PATH = \"../data/test_16k.wav\"\nvad = VAD(SR)\n# Use get_speech_timestamps to get \n# start and end timestamps of speech segments\ntimestamps = vad.get_speech_timestamps(WAV_PATH)\nfor _ in timestamps:\n    print(_)\n\n# You shuold get the following output:\n# {'segment': 0, 'start': 26560, 'end': 48704}\n# {'segment': 1, 'start': 71616, 'end': 106048}\n# {'segment': 2, 'start': 149952, 'end': 185920}\n\n# Use get_speech_probs to get probabilities for each chunk\nprobs = vad.get_speech_probs(WAV_PATH)\nfor _ in probs:\n    print(_)\n# You shuold get the following output:\n# 0.02\n# 0.01\n# 0.01\n# 0.01\n# 0.0\n```\n\n2. `VAD` class with noise suppression\nYou just need to set `denoise=True` when initializing `VAD` class.\n```python\nvad = VAD(SR, denoise=True)\n```\nPlease note that: func:`get_speech_probs` may not work well with noise suppression.\n\n3. `VADIterator` class\nPlease refer to `ws_app/ws_server.py` for more details.\n\n\n"], "modules": [{"name": "dguard_vad.utils", "documentation": ["coding = utf-8", "@Time    : 2024-12-10  12:42:58", "@Author  : zhaosheng@nuaa.edu.cn", "@Describe: Dguard VAD utils"], "functions": [{"name": "dguard_vad.utils.get_energy", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "chunk", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "sr", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "from_harmonic", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "to_harmonic", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "dguard_vad.frame_queue", "documentation": ["coding = utf-8", "@Time    : 2024-12-10  12:42:29", "@Author  : zhaosheng@nuaa.edu.cn", "@Describe: Frame queue for VAD."], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "dguard_vad.frame_queue.queue", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "dguard_vad.frame_queue.frames", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [{"name": "dguard_vad.frame_queue.FrameQueue", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "dguard_vad.frame_queue.FrameQueue.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "frame_size", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "in_rate", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "speech_pad_samples", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "out_rate", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "padding", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "dguard_vad.frame_queue.FrameQueue.add_chunk", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "chunk", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "is_last", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "dguard_vad.frame_queue.FrameQueue.get_frame", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "speech_padding", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}], "exports": []}, {"name": "dguard_vad.pickable_session", "documentation": ["coding = utf-8", "@Time    : 2024-12-10  12:42:42", "@Author  : zhaosheng@nuaa.edu.cn", "@Describe: Pickable session for VAD."], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "dguard_vad.pickable_session.vad_session", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [{"name": "dguard_vad.pickable_session.PickableSession", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "dguard_vad.pickable_session.PickableSession.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "onnx_path", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "dguard_vad.pickable_session.PickableSession.run", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "*args", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "dguard_vad.pickable_session.PickableSession.__getstate__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "dguard_vad.pickable_session.PickableSession.__setstate__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "values", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["This is a wrapper to make the current InferenceSession class pickable."]}], "exports": []}, {"name": "dguard_vad.dguard_vad", "documentation": ["coding = utf-8", "@Time    : 2024-12-10  12:42:03", "@Author  : zhaosheng@nuaa.edu.cn", "@Describe: VAD Model and Iterator definition."], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "dguard_vad.dguard_vad.VAD", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "dguard_vad.dguard_vad.VAD.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "sample_rate", "type": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "threshold", "type": {"name": "float", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.float", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "min_silence_duration_ms", "type": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "speech_pad_ms", "type": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "denoise", "type": {"name": "bool", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bool", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Init silero VAD model\n\nParameters\n----------\nsample_rate: int (default - 16000)\n    sample rate of the input audio\nthreshold: float (default - 0.5)\n    Speech threshold. Silero VAD outputs speech probabilities for each audio\n    chunk, probabilities ABOVE this value are considered as SPEECH. It is\n    better to tune this parameter for each dataset separately, but \"lazy\"\n    0.5 is pretty good for most datasets.\nmin_silence_duration_ms: int (default - 300 milliseconds)\n    In the end of each speech chunk wait for min_silence_duration_ms before\n    separating it.\nspeech_pad_ms: int (default - 100 milliseconds)\n    Final speech chunks are padded by speech_pad_ms each side.\ndenoise: bool (default - False)\n    whether denoise the audio samples."]}, {"name": "dguard_vad.dguard_vad.VAD.reset", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "dguard_vad.dguard_vad.VAD.__call__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "x", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "sr", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "dguard_vad.dguard_vad.VAD.denoise_chunk", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "denoiser", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "chunk", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "is_last", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "dguard_vad.dguard_vad.VAD.add_chunk", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "chunk", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "is_last", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "dguard_vad.dguard_vad.VAD.read_audio", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "wav_path", "type": {"name": "Union", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Union", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, {"name": "Path", "xref": {"fqname": "pathlib.Path", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "dguard_vad.dguard_vad.VAD.get_speech_probs", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "wav_path", "type": {"name": "Union", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Union", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, {"name": "Path", "xref": {"fqname": "pathlib.Path", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Getting speech probabilities of audio frames (32ms/frame)\n\nParameters\n----------\nwav_path: wav path\n\nReturns\n----------\nspeech_probs: list of speech probabilities"]}, {"name": "dguard_vad.dguard_vad.VAD.process_segment", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "segment", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "wav", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "save_path", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "flat_layout", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "return_seconds", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "dguard_vad.dguard_vad.VAD.get_speech_timestamps", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "wav_path", "type": {"name": "Union", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Union", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, {"name": "Path", "xref": {"fqname": "pathlib.Path", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "default": null}, {"name": "save_path", "type": {"name": "Union", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Union", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, {"name": "Path", "xref": {"fqname": "pathlib.Path", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "flat_layout", "type": {"name": "bool", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bool", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "min_speech_duration_ms", "type": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "max_speech_duration_s", "type": {"name": "float", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.float", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "return_seconds", "type": {"name": "bool", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bool", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Splitting long audios into speech chunks using silero VAD\n\nParameters\n----------\nwav_path: wav path\nsave_path: string or Path (default - None)\n    whether the save speech segments\nflat_layout: bool (default - True)\n    whether use the flat directory structure\nmin_speech_duration_ms: int (default - 250 milliseconds)\n    Final speech chunks shorter min_speech_duration_ms are thrown out\nmax_speech_duration_s: int (default - inf)\n    Maximum duration of speech chunks in seconds\n    Chunks longer than max_speech_duration_s will be split at the timestamp\n    of the last silence that lasts more than 98ms (if any), to prevent\n    agressive cutting. Otherwise, they will be split aggressively just\n    before max_speech_duration_s.\nreturn_seconds: bool (default - False)\n    whether return timestamps in seconds (default - samples)\n\nReturns\n----------\nspeeches: list of dicts\n    list containing ends and beginnings of speech chunks (samples or seconds\n    based on return_seconds)"]}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}, {"name": "dguard_vad.dguard_vad.VADIterator", "bases": ["VAD"], "methods": [{"name": "dguard_vad.dguard_vad.VADIterator.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "sample_rate", "type": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "threshold", "type": {"name": "float", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.float", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "min_silence_duration_ms", "type": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "speech_pad_ms", "type": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "denoise", "type": {"name": "bool", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bool", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Class for stream imitation"]}, {"name": "dguard_vad.dguard_vad.VADIterator.reset", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "dguard_vad.dguard_vad.VADIterator.get_frame", "asynchronous": fa